    {
        "content": "<p>I have another question,a:ℝ,a&gt;=0,how to prove (a ^ 3) ^ (2 / 3)=a^2? <span aria-label=\"joy\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f602\" role=\"img\" title=\"joy\">:joy:</span></p>",
        "id": 471182077,
        "sender_full_name": "Zihao Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1726642307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's best to ask questions in the form of a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a> here. That way it's easy to see unambiguously what the question is and also easier to answer it. It's almost clear what the mwe is here (I guess there are issues with the type of 2/3) but I'm just trying to encourage good practice :-)</p>",
        "id": 471190593,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1726645312
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A vague answer: just search the library (eg using loogle) for theorems which mention (a^b)^c and you'll find the one you want :-)</p>",
        "id": 471191069,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1726645478
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110038\">@Kevin Buzzard</span> sorry,I am just new in learning lean,so what is loogle in lean4?</p>",
